A Process memory layout is as below

STACK :: It grows downwards
=====

Memory Mapping Segment  :: File mappings(including dynamic libraries) and anonymous mappings. i.e.  /lib/libc.so (It also grows downwards)
======================

HEAP  :: It grows upwards
======
BSS  :: Un-Initialized static variables;
======
DATA :: Initialized static variables;
=====
TEXT :: Stores the binary image of the process.

References: https://manybutfinite.com/post/anatomy-of-a-program-in-memory/
https://gist.github.com/CMCDragonkai/10ab53654b2aa6ce55c11cfc5b2432a4


Process resources
==================
maximum size of core files
maximum size of a process's data segment
maximum size of files created
maximum size that may be locked into memory
maximum size of resident memory
maximum number of file descriptors open at one time
maximum size of the stack
maximum amount of cpu time used
maximum number of processes allowed
maximum size of virtual memory available

Reference:: https://serverfault.com/a/497207


